node.title: New Omicron case found in NSW, has been active in community
node.description: The number of cases of the Omicron COVID-19 variant grows to five after a new infection is discovered. The ABC understands a woman in her 30s visited several venues on the Central Coast while infectious.
node.content: ["The ABC has confirmed there is now a fifth case of the Omicron variant of COVID-19 in NSW.", "The case is a woman in her 30s who arrived in Sydney on Saturday, before new travel restrictions were in place.", "She had travelled to at least two southern African countries prior to arriving.", "It is understood she has visited several venues on the NSW Central Coast.", "Meanwhile, urgent genomic sequencing is underway to probe whether two confirmed COVID-19 cases that arrived in Sydney on Thursday from overseas have the Omicron variant.", "Health officials said the pair flew from Doha on flight QR908 on Thursday and both are isolating at their homes.", "All passengers on the Doha flight must be tested immediately, regardless of previous test results and vaccination status, and isolate until a negative result is received.", "Four travellers from southern Africa who arrived in Sydney over the weekend have since tested positive to the Omicron variant.", "They are all fully vaccinated and isolating in special health accommodation.", "The only other recorded Omicron case\u00a0in Australia is a man who has been at the Howard Springs\u00a0quarantine facility since arriving from South Africa on November 25.", "The World Health Organization has classified Omicron as a \"variant of concern\" but said further research was\u00a0needed to assess its potential to escape protection against immunity induced by vaccines and previous infections.", "NSW recorded 179 new COVID-19 cases an three deaths in the 24 hours to 8pm last night.", "A man in his 50s from Tamworth who had underlying health conditions died at Tamworth Base Hospital. He had received one dose of a COVID-19 vaccine.", "A woman in her 60s with underlying health conditions died\u00a0at St Vincent\u2019s Hospital in Sydney's east.\u00a0She had received one dose of a COVID-19 vaccine.", "A man in his 40s from Western Sydney who also had underlying health conditions and was partially vaccinated died at Nepean Hospital.", "More to come."]
